Here is a **clean, focused ROADMAP for becoming a Windows + Qt C++ Desktop Application Developer (2025)**.

This roadmap is tailored specifically for **Windows platform + Qt Widgets/QML** + **C++ development workflow**.

---

# üöÄ **Windows + Qt Desktop Developer Roadmap (C++ 2025)**

---

# 1Ô∏è‚É£ **C++ Core (Required Before Qt)**

You must know modern C++ basics:

### ‚úî Language

* Variables, functions, pointers, references
* Classes, structs, constructors, RAII
* Operator overloading
* Inheritance + polymorphism
* Templates basics
* C++17 features:

  * `auto`, `nullptr`
  * `unique_ptr`, `shared_ptr`
  * lambda
  * move semantics

### ‚úî STL

* `std::vector`, `std::string`, `std::map`
* Algorithms (`sort`, `find`, `transform`)
* `std::optional`, `std::variant` (modern design)

---

# 2Ô∏è‚É£ **Tools You Must Learn (Windows Specific)**

### ‚úî Compiler & IDE

* **MSVC (Visual Studio 2022+)**
* **Qt Creator** (cross-platform IDE)
* Optional: CLion (CMake + Qt integration)

### ‚úî Build System (Very Important)

* **CMake** ‚Üí Primary tool for Qt + C++ projects in 2025
* Ninja (optional)

### ‚úî Debugging

* Visual Studio debugger
* Qt Creator debugger
* Breakpoints, inspecting widgets, memory checks

---

# 3Ô∏è‚É£ **Qt Fundamentals (Start Here)**

## ‚úî Qt Core

Learn these modules first:

* QObject
* Signals and Slots
* QVariant
* QString / QStringList
* QFile, QDir (File handling)
* QTimer
* Qt event loop
* QDebug

## ‚úî Qt Widgets (Traditional Desktop UI)

* QWidget
* QMainWindow
* QPushButton, QLabel, QLineEdit
* QVBoxLayout, QHBoxLayout, QGridLayout
* QAction / QMenu / QToolBar
* QFileDialog
* QMessageBox

---

# 4Ô∏è‚É£ **Qt Intermediate Level**

## ‚úî Model/View Architecture

Very important for large projects:

* QListView / QTableView / QTreeView
* QStringListModel
* QStandardItemModel
* Custom models (QAbstractListModel, QAbstractTableModel)

## ‚úî Qt Graphics

* QPainter
* Custom drawing
* Rendering images, shapes, text

## ‚úî Qt Networking

* QNetworkAccessManager
* REST API calls
* JSON handling (QJsonDocument)

## ‚úî Qt Concurrency

* QThread
* QRunnable + QThreadPool
* Signals/slots between threads

## ‚úî Qt SQL

* SQLite + Qt SQL classes
* QSqlDatabase, QSqlQuery
* Model-based views with SQL tables

---

# 5Ô∏è‚É£ **Qt QML + Qt Quick (Optional but Future-Proof)**

If you want modern UI (animations, mobile):

* QML basics
* Qt Quick Controls
* Binding system
* Integrating C++ backend with QML front-end
* Q_PROPERTY + NOTIFY
* Custom QML components

---

# 6Ô∏è‚É£ **Windows-Specific Skills (Important)**

### ‚úî Win32 Basics

Qt hides Windows APIs, but you still need basics:

* Registry read/write
* Windows paths
* DPI scaling (important for Qt apps)
* Win32 native file dialogs (optional)

### ‚úî Deployment on Windows

Learn packaging:

* windeployqt (Qt deployment tool)
* MSVC Redistributables
* Creating Installers:

  * NSIS
  * Inno Setup
  * MSI
  * MSIX

### ‚úî Performance

* Memory leaks (Valgrind-like tools on Windows ‚Üí Dr. Memory)
* Optimize large UI apps
* Using QElapsedTimer to measure speed

---

# 7Ô∏è‚É£ **Architecture & Patterns (Professional Level)**

### ‚≠ê Must learn patterns for Qt apps:

* Observer ‚Üí Signals/Slots
* Singleton
* Factory Method
* MVC / MVVM (QML loves MVVM)
* Command pattern
* Strategy pattern
* State machine (Qt has QStateMachine)

### ‚≠ê App Layering

* UI ‚Üí Business Logic ‚Üí Data Access
* Separating widgets from logic (clean architecture)

---

# 8Ô∏è‚É£ **Real Projects to Practice**

### Beginner

* Basic calculator
* Notes app (save/load text)
* Timer app

### Intermediate

* Todo app (SQLite + widgets)
* File explorer with tree view
* Weather dashboard with REST API
* Image viewer + filters
* Audio player (Qt Multimedia)

### Advanced

* Trading dashboard (REST API + charts)
* A plugin-based Qt UI tool
* Custom IDE-like tool (dock widgets)
* QML cross-platform app
* Real-time graph visualization
* Network monitoring dashboard

These are the kinds of projects companies look for.

---

# 9Ô∏è‚É£ **Final Step: Professional Development**

### ‚úî Git + GitHub

* Branching
* Pull requests
* Code reviews

### ‚úî Coding Standards

* Google C++ Style Guide
* Qt coding style

### ‚úî Testing

* Qt Test
* Unit test for business logic

